  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  10&lt;=NIHSS Score=&lt;25

          -  Symptoms onset less than 4 hours

          -  Occlusion of the intracranial carotid, the middle cerebral artery (M1) or the upper
             third of the basilar

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Contraindications for intravenous thrombolysis

          -  Occlusion or stenosis of the pre-occlusive cervical internal carotid artery
             ipsilateral to the lesion

          -  Any cause local prohibiting femoral catheterization
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
